# Environment Variables for Deployment

# JWT Secret - Generate a strong random string for production
# You can generate one with: openssl rand -base64 32
JWT_SECRET=your-super-secret-jwt-key-change-this-in-production

# Upstash Redis (KV) - Set automatically by Vercel when you add the Upstash for Redis integration
# Vercel prefixes these with the integration/store name (e.g. "profile" â†’ profile_KV_REST_API_URL).
# The app auto-detects any variable matching *_KV_REST_API_URL / *_KV_REST_API_TOKEN,
# so no manual configuration is needed after connecting the integration.
#
# Example variable names (prefix depends on your store name in Vercel):
# profile_KV_REST_API_URL=https://your-store.upstash.io
# profile_KV_REST_API_TOKEN=your-kv-token
# profile_KV_REST_API_READ_ONLY_TOKEN=your-kv-read-only-token
# profile_KV_URL=rediss://default:your-token@your-store.upstash.io:6379
# profile_REDIS_URL=rediss://default:your-token@your-store.upstash.io:6379

# Note: Without Redis, achievements will be stored in memory and reset on each deployment
